"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-olympics-cycling-ollie-wood-madison-paris-b2594518.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Notifications\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 13}, {\"ngram\": \"browser preferences\", \"from\": 32, \"to\": 51}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in Swipe for next article Ollie Wood was wiped out by Jan-Willem van Schip, of the Netherlands, in an incident that appeared to involve head-to-head contact Removed from bookmarks I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998095450063, \"rank\": 1.6840464098124208e-07, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 77}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 105}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 117}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"your browser\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"Swipe\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 196}, {\"ngram\": \"next article\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 213}, {\"ngram\": \"Ollie Wood\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 224}, {\"ngram\": \"Jan-Willem van Schip\", \"from\": 242, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"an incident\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"bookmarks\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 367}, {\"ngram\": \"offers\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 427}, {\"ngram\": \"The Independent\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice Team GBcyclist Ollie Wood felt like a 'crash test dummy' after being dramatically wiped out by a Dutch opponent during a mad Olympic Madison in Paris.\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.999603936242736, \"rank\": 0.00039002084485830315, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.347229613243602e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"Team GBcyclist Ollie Wood\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 502}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'crash test dummy\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 532}, {\"ngram\": \"a mad Olympic Madison\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wood, 28, was controversially taken down with 40 laps to go during the chaotic event as there appeared to be head-to-head contact between him and Jan-Willem van Schip.\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wood\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 634}, {\"ngram\": \"40 laps\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"the chaotic event\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 714}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"Jan-Willem van Schip\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB did not complain about Van Schip's move, but the Dutch team were later disqualified from the race and Van Schip fined 1,000CHF (\\u00a3720) for a \\\"blow with the helmet\\\" according to the commissaires' decision.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999826636669, \"rank\": 1.6853852809594682e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 856, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.999603936242736, \"rank\": 0.00039002084485830315, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Schip's move\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Schip\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"1,000CHF\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"blow\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 952}, {\"ngram\": \"the helmet\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 968}, {\"ngram\": \"the commissaires' decision\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wood's racing line looked to be intentionally intercepted as he was inexplicably sent plummeting to the canvas in front of a stunned V\\u00e9lodrome National de Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines crowd.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wood's racing line\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"the canvas\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"-Yvelines\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident meant Team GB lost a crucial lap and 20 points as they ended up finishing 10thout of 15 teams while Portugal grabbed gold ahead of Italy.\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999826636669, \"rank\": 1.6853852809594682e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1314, \"end\": 1322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998117887294, \"rank\": 1.873339532470345e-07, \"text\": \"Portugal\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995753100105625, \"rank\": 0.0004248054129276937, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The incident\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"a crucial lap\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1246}, {\"ngram\": \"20 points\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"10thout\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"15 teams\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking about the collision, Wood, 28, said: \\\"I will be fine and live to fight another day.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the collision\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"Wood\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not my first crash but it's a bit different when you get hit from behind and you do not see it coming.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my first crash\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There were a lot of resting riders, so he probably thought instead of a high line, he'd cut it fine and he ploughed into me.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"resting riders\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"a high line\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have got no clue [if it was a clash of heads] - I just got hit really hard from behind by the biggest rider on the track.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no clue\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"a clash\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"heads\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest rider\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone's cognitive functions started to decline at one given point pretty rapidly - there were lots of lapses of concentration and when there are people all over the track, wheels colliding is inevitable.\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone's cognitive functions\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"one given point\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1912}, {\"ngram\": \"lapses\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"concentration\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1939}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1965}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"wheels colliding\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2002}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He hit me so hard, I felt like a crash test dummy.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a crash test dummy\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, I just did not have the legs to execute it today.\\\"\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2130, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the legs\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teammate Mark Stewart, who was forced to rush back onto the track to resume the race after the incident, added: \\\"I thought if I wasn't already suffering, I am going to suffer now!\\\"\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2141, \"end\": 2153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Stewart_(English_musician)\", \"score\": 0.8747509874581362, \"rank\": 0.06241426611798487, \"text\": \"Mark Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Stewart_(English_musician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Stewart_(English_musician)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2216}, {\"ngram\": \"the incident\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stewart, who won Madison World Championship silver in Glasgow alongside Wood last year, only discovered he would be racing on Saturday morning after being given an indication by Hayter the previous evening.\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stewart_Grand_Prix\", \"score\": 0.9999999095198332, \"rank\": 7.29400067681245e-08, \"text\": \"Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stewart_Grand_Prix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stewart_Grand_Prix\"}, {\"begin\": 2331, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9968445269186061, \"rank\": 0.0031654616102442844, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}, {\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"score\": 0.9999999895844667, \"rank\": 8.73416664185983e-09, \"text\": \"World Championship\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\"}, {\"begin\": 2368, \"end\": 2375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9989994735257729, \"rank\": 0.0010015285299524335, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wood\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2390}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday morning\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"an indication\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"Hayter\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hayter had combined with Dan Bigham, Charlie Tanfield and Ethan Vernon to scoop team pursuit silver behind Australia in midweek but was forced to withdraw from the Madison with a calf injury.\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2559, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlie Tanfield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\"}, {\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Vernon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\"}, {\"begin\": 2629, \"end\": 2638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9817177386463825, \"rank\": 0.01862064225033144, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9968445269186061, \"rank\": 0.0031654616102442844, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hayter\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2528}, {\"ngram\": \"Dan Bigham\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2557}, {\"ngram\": \"team\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2606}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"midweek\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"a calf injury\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And asked about his eleventh-hour call-up, Stewart said: \\\"You have got to be ready to race the whole time and all, credit to Ethan - I saw how deep he went in those team pursuits and you can see he wasn't right.\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2758, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stewart_Grand_Prix\", \"score\": 0.9999999095198332, \"rank\": 7.29400067681245e-08, \"text\": \"Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stewart_Grand_Prix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stewart_Grand_Prix\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his eleventh-hour call-up\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2756}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole time\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"Ethan\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"those team pursuits\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought there was a chance I'd get the call and I took the role seriously.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 2957}, {\"ngram\": \"the call\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 2974}, {\"ngram\": \"the role\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 2994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a horrendous mix of the worst nerves ever and confidence - we are high performance athletes, have amazing support from British Cycling so you do go out there with confidence.\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3134, \"end\": 3149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a horrendous mix\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"the worst nerves\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3051}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3071}, {\"ngram\": \"high performance athletes\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"amazing support\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3128}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But you have also got this contrasting thing of it being the most nervous you have ever been in your life.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this contrasting thing\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3236}, {\"ngram\": \"your life\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3297}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ethan gave me a heads up yesterday and I said 'take all the time you need' as he's been phenomenal.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ethan\", \"from\": 3301, \"to\": 3306}, {\"ngram\": \"a heads\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3322}, {\"ngram\": \"all the time\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We just struggled to make an impression - we knew it was going to be hot and fast because this is theOlympics, so we rode relatively conservatively but at the end of the day our legs never came out.\\\"\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an impression\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3442}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 3501, \"to\": 3512}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3565}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"our legs\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the evening, Jack Carlin kicked off his latest pursuit of a long-awaited major gold medal by progressing to the men's keirin quarter-finals.\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3628, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9697650148057427, \"rank\": 0.02331094765097423, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}, {\"begin\": 3633, \"end\": 3639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999999307151508, \"rank\": 6.928489154814515e-08, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evening\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"his latest pursuit\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3669}, {\"ngram\": \"a long-awaited major gold medal\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3704}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's keirin quarter-finals\", \"from\": 3723, \"to\": 3754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paisley peddler, 27, won team sprint silver and individual bronze earlier this week and got his third and final campaign underway in straightforward fashion.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Paisley\", \"score\": 0.9999995420804364, \"rank\": 4.5791989905159835e-07, \"text\": \"Paisley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q1